=== Noun ===
'''{{PAGENAME}}''' ([[おんよみ]], ''[[on'yomi]]'')

# The [[reading]] (''yomi'') (i.e. [[pronunciation]]) of a Japanese word written in [[kanji]] that is roughly based on the pronunciation of the kanji characters in the main Chinese dialects at the time the word was introduced to Japan.  
#: As words written in kanji were brought to Japan at different times rather than all at once, ''on'yomi'' are categorized as ''[[goon]]'' ([[呉音]], [[ごおん]]), ''[[kan'on]]'' ([[漢音]], [[かんおん]]), and ''[[tōon]]'' ([[唐音]], [[とうおん]]), depending on when that particular ''on'yomi'' became common and so which dialect was used by those in power in China.  Thus, the same kanji may be used to mean different things depending on the reading, reflecting the differences between the original dialects, such as [[利益]] which means "[[profit]]" when read with the ''kan'on'' pronunciation [[りえき]], but means "[[Buddhist]] [[blessing]] or [[salvation]]" when read with the ''goon'' pronunciation [[りやく]].  
#: ''On'yomi'' loosely corresponds to ''[[kango]]'' ([[漢語]], [[かんご]]), with ''on'yomi'' signifying the reading and ''kango'' signifying the actual word itself.  

